If you can make scanline rendering significantly faster than pixel rendering, go ahead and use it. PocketNES (a fork of LoopyNES for GBA) uses scanline rendering so that it can take advantage of the underlying platform's 2D acceleration, and Dwedit can tell you about the smart approximations it does to make tricky games like Marble Madness look decent despite the fact.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Mar 11, 2010 7:06 am</p><hr />
