Actually, the 3rd technique of pixel based rendering is used in several emulators. And no it's not hard, infact it's pretty easy in my opinion. But it's very slow unless you optimize it.<br /><br />For most games, scanline rendering will work fine. LoopyNES is a good NES emulator but I don't believe it uses pixel based rendering.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Thu Mar 11, 2010 12:36 am</p><hr />
